<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Commandment" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Commandment,</orth> 1) command, order: <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.109" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.238" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 238</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.329" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 329</bibl> <cit><quote>(do).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.381" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 381</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.381" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 381</bibl> <cit><quote>have I c. on the pulse of life?</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.92" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 92</bibl></cit>. <emph>At a person's c.</emph> == at his service: <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 33</bibl> (Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>command</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 3, 142</bibl>. <emph>At c.</emph> == at pleasure: <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 2, 27</bibl>.<lb />2) a precept of the decalogue: <cit><quote>the ten --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 8</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 8</bibl> Ludicrously, <emph>my ten --s</emph> == my ten fingers: <cit><quote>I'ld set my ten --s in your face,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.145" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 145</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>